    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water </strong>with your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> (the same as you would for pasta)</p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-bulgur-salad-with-green-chutney/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p><p>Add your <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Transfer the <strong>toasted cumin seeds</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> (save the pan for later!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-bulgur-salad-with-green-chutney/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-bulgur-salad-with-green-chutney/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice your <strong>courgette[s]</strong> into quarters lengthways, then chop into bite-size pieces</p><p>Chop your<strong> coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-bulgur-salad-with-green-chutney/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>cumin seeds</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1/3 of the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> in the <strong>pestle & mortar </strong>and grind to a smooth paste</p><p>Add 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span><strong> olive oil</strong> and your <strong>rice vinegar </strong>then season generously with<strong> salt </strong>and<strong> pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>green</strong> <strong>chutney</strong></p><p>Tip: Don't have a pestle & mortar? Pulse in a food processor instead!</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-bulgur-salad-with-green-chutney/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat and add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong> and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped courgette</strong> and cook for 6-8 min or until tender</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-bulgur-salad-with-green-chutney/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the courgette is cooked, fluff the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>bulgur </strong>with a fork and add to the pan</p><p>Break your <strong>goats' cheese</strong> into chunks</p><p>Stir <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>goats' cheese chunks </strong>and <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>green</strong> <strong>chutney</strong> through the bulgur<strong> </strong>(save the rest for the garnish!) \u2013 this is your <strong>goats' cheese & bulgur salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/goats-cheese-and-bulgur-salad-with-green-chutney/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>goats' cheese & bulgur salad</strong> with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>goats' cheese chunks</strong> and <strong>green</strong> <strong>chutney</strong> over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
